001package io.github.ai4ci.config;
002
003import io.github.ai4ci.flow.output.ExportSelector;
004import io.github.ai4ci.output.ImmutableContactCSV;
005import io.github.ai4ci.output.ImmutableDebugParametersCSV;
006import io.github.ai4ci.output.ImmutableInfectivityProfileCSV;
007import io.github.ai4ci.output.ImmutableLineListCSV;
008import io.github.ai4ci.output.ImmutableOutbreakBehaviourCountCSV;
009import io.github.ai4ci.output.ImmutableOutbreakCSV;
010import io.github.ai4ci.output.ImmutableOutbreakContactCountCSV;
011import io.github.ai4ci.output.ImmutableOutbreakFinalStateCSV;
012import io.github.ai4ci.output.ImmutableOutbreakHistoryCSV;
013import io.github.ai4ci.output.ImmutablePersonDemographicsCSV;
014
015/**
016 * Enumeration of the different exporters available in the system, each
017 * associated with an export selector.
018 *
019 * <p>
020 * This enum provides a convenient way to reference and manage the various
021 * exporters used for outputting different types of data during the simulation.
022 * Each exporter is linked to a specific CSV format and export stage, as defined
023 * by their respective selectors.
024 *
025 * @author Rob Challen
026 */
027public enum Exporters {
028
029        /**
030         * Exporter for outbreak summary data, using the ImmutableOutbreakCSV format.
031         */
032        SUMMARY(
033                        ExportSelector.of(ImmutableOutbreakCSV.class)
034        ),
035        /** Exporter for line list data, using the ImmutableLineListCSV format. */
036        LINELIST(
037                        ExportSelector.of(ImmutableLineListCSV.class)
038        ),
039        /**
040         * Exporter for historical test data, using the ImmutableOutbreakHistoryCSV
041         * format.
042         */
043        HISTORICAL_TESTS(
044                        ExportSelector.of(ImmutableOutbreakHistoryCSV.class)
045        ),
046        /**
047         * Exporter for contact network data, using the ImmutableContactCSV format.
048         */
049        CONTACT_NETWORK(
050                        ExportSelector.of(ImmutableContactCSV.class)
051        ),
052        /**
053         * Exporter for infectivity profile data, using the
054         * ImmutableInfectivityProfileCSV format.
055         */
056        INFECTIVITY_PROFILE(
057                        ExportSelector.of(ImmutableInfectivityProfileCSV.class)
058        ),
059        /**
060         * Exporter for person demographic data, using the
061         * ImmutablePersonDemographicsCSV format.
062         */
063        DEMOGRAPHICS(
064                        ExportSelector.of(ImmutablePersonDemographicsCSV.class)
065        ),
066        /**
067         * Exporter for debug parameters, using the ImmutableDebugParametersCSV
068         * format.
069         */
070        DEBUG_PARAMETERS(
071                        ExportSelector.of(ImmutableDebugParametersCSV.class)
072        ),
073        /**
074         * Exporter for final state data, using the ImmutableOutbreakFinalStateCSV
075         * format.
076         */
077        FINAL_STATE(
078                        ExportSelector.of(ImmutableOutbreakFinalStateCSV.class)
079        ),
080        /**
081         * Exporter for behaviour count data, using the
082         * ImmutableOutbreakBehaviourCountCSV format.
083         */
084        BEHAVIOUR(
085                        ExportSelector.of(ImmutableOutbreakBehaviourCountCSV.class)
086        ),
087        /**
088         * Exporter for contact count data, using the
089         * ImmutableOutbreakContactCountCSV format.
090         */
091        CONTACT_COUNTS(
092                        ExportSelector.of(ImmutableOutbreakContactCountCSV.class)
093        );
094
095        private ExportSelector<?> selector;
096
097        private Exporters(ExportSelector<?> selector) {
098                this.selector = selector;
099        }
100
101        /**
102         * Get the export selector associated with this exporter.
103         *
104         * @return the ExportSelector instance that defines how to extract and format
105         *         data for this exporter
106         */
107        ExportSelector<?> getSelector() { return this.selector; }
108
109}
